Title: Supply & Delivery of Visualisation Equipment part funded by the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) Ref: 36R17P01698
Description:
This is a confirmation of award following the below tender. The original advert read as follows:

The University of Chester is seeking tenders for the Supply and Delivery of Visualisation Equipment to the University Centre Shrewsbury Campus. This is for the Digital Solutions project funded by the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) Ref: 36R17P01698. 

This tender is to secure the supply and delivery of equipment to construct a Visualisation Suite that will enable the creation of 360 degree and 3D imagery videos and make them available to SMEs and care providers for social media channels, personal digital assistants and online platforms. The Visualisation Suite will include editing functions so that footage captured in the field can be edited for the above use. The period of contract is until 31st December 2020 however the initial anticipated requirements, as listed within Document 2 - Specification and Pricing Schedule, are to be delivered by 23rd November 2018 (estimated TBC). 
Whilst the anticipated contract value, based on indicative quantities within this tender is approximated at £50,000 to £60,000 including VAT, actual demand and volumes may vary from the indicative values given in this tender, as over the period of the contract term, additional requirements may be identified, or reduced, as demand may increase or alter.  

Please note that the Digital Solutions project has a limited budget within which it is endeavouring to source all its equipment and tenderers are therefore strongly encouraged to submit their most "cost effective" options that most closely meets at least the minimum specification as detailed within the attached workbook "Document 2 - Specification & Pricing Schedule".
Additional Text:
To participate in this opportunity tenderers were asked to Express an Interest via our In-Tend portal, they were then able to access the tender documents.

Please note that where you may have previously registered with In-Tend, it will be necessary for you to ensure that your registration does include being registered to see opportunities for University of Chester. Registration to this site is free for suppliers. There is also Help/Guidance on how to use the supplier site on the 'Help' section of the site: https://in-tendhost.co.uk/universityofchester/aspx/Help Tender documents must be completed and returned via In-Tend by 12:00 Noon on Monday 19th November 2018.

Title: 017/2019FC Summer AV Works 2019 - AWARD
Description:
This project is to upgrade or commission numerous teaching spaces around Frenchay and Glenside Campuses. There are 4 lots comprising of Lecture Theatres, Large Teaching Spaces, Standard Teaching Spaces, Teaching spaces with Display Panels as opposed to projectors/lecterns. 
      
      This forms part of a wider University masterplan project which aims to create new buildings and refurbishments to cater for the ever changing requirements and demands of the HE sector.
      
      The University's ambitions include being professionally recognised and practice-orientated, connected to our local and regional economy, being digitally advanced and agile and to have a global approach. We prioritise providing an engaging and outstanding learning, teaching and support service to our students and ensuring our graduates are ready and able for their chosen field of employment.

Title: AV Refresh
Description: The current Audio Visual (AV) estate at Birmingham City University (BCU) has been reviewed and certain equipment has been identified as having reached the end of its hardware lifecycle and is in need of replacement. The objective of the AV Refresh project is to not only modernise but also to rationalise the University's diverse AV estate in order to ensure that the end-user experience is more consistent between rooms and campuses. The procurement will provide the opportunity to facilitate new methods of academic delivery and where possible some rooms may be re-orientated to accommodate those visions. It is anticipated that this will also increase staff productivity and improve the student experience.
